pdc_describe.title: Load file list directly from AWS

comments.body:
We can get a download url from an [aws presigner](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/sdk-for-ruby/v3/api/Aws/S3/Presigner.html). It works by default for 15 minutes.
```
work = Work.first
service = S3QueryService.new(work)
files = service.client_s3_files
signer = Aws::S3::Presigner.new(client: service.client)
url = signer.presigned_url(:get_object, bucket: service.bucket_name, key: files[0].key)
```

princeton_ansible.title: [lib-jobs] peoplesoft mount doesn't always mount when required

comments.body:
Notes from Ansible Open House today - things we tested:
- check the contents of the registered `mount_info` variable (not super helpful, no module-specific return values)
- manually `umount` the disk, then test the role with lines 41-50 deleted (just using `mounted`), this seems to fix the current problem
- manually remove the listing from the fstab, then test the role with lines 41-50 deleted - this also worked

Other ideas:
- explore running an ad-hoc task using `remounted` state (instead of `mounted` and/or `present`) if we see the original bad state again
